      "date": "2013-09-05 23:59:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nThe main problem I see with this approach is that there is always going to be some extra combination of devices or symlinks that is going to confuse this code.  It would be better to have some kind of direct check to see if the device is mounted (e.g. checking /proc/fs/lustre/*/*/mntdev or similar).",
